message:
The most reliable path to a strong base score (30) is to pick a single small animal (like a lizard or frog), apply 'mutation catalyst' twice to make it 'super-mutant', then apply 'growth serum' three times to make it 'ultra-grown'. This yields an item with a value of 30.

To increase your score further, combine items with different habitats (land, water, air) to create basic hybrids (e.g., pufferfish + bird yields value 5). Then, combine your 'ultra-grown super-mutant' animal (value 30) with one of these basic hybrids. This usually results in an item with a value around 35-40, containing the original components (e.g., grown pufferfish, grown bird, ultra-grown super-mutant lizard).

The key to reaching 50-60 is to apply 'growth serum' to this new complex item. This will cause its previously unprocessed components (e.g., 'pufferfish', 'bird') to become 'grown', 'super-grown', and eventually 'ultra-grown' while increasing the item's value substantially. Be cautious with the 'mutation catalyst' on complex items, as it often introduces 'corrupted' features, which severely drops the item's value, or turns 'super-mutant' into 'corrupted'.
